==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rockrose
<hw>Rock"rose`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
name given to any species of the genus <gen>Helianthemum</gen>, low
shrubs or herbs with yellow flowers, especially the European
<spn>Helianthemum vulgare</spn> and the American frostweed,
<spn>Helianthemum Canadense</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cretan rockrose</b></col>, <cd>a related shrub
(<spn>Cistus Creticus</spn>), one of the plants yielding the fragrant
gum called <prod>ladanum</prod>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rock shaft</ent>⟦br⟧
